In 432 cases, it was concluded that the asylum seeker was “possibly under 18 years of age”.
The tests were carried out only in cases where there was reason to doubt the age stated by the applicant.
Johan Göransson, from the Forensics Office, says the results are consistent with the results of previous months.
"The figures are fairly consistent, and there are no big differences from previous months' figures," he told The Local.
While a large number of applicants were determined to be over 18 years of age, this does not necessarily mean that applicants have lied about their age.
